A word of warning to anons coming over: do to its p2p nature and the need for verifiable ownership ZeroNet is built on an accout system. This means if you're not careful everything you post on 08chan can be tied to a single "username" which anyone can lookup to find what you've posted and what boards you own. For example I know that >>0c74426b-de0f-4499-92fd-56c34bb4a62a is the owner of /fur/ and has posted on /b/, /tech/, /v/, and /sci/.

If you're paranoid you could nuke you ZeroNet install directory periodically  to reset your users.json file. You could also look into the multiuser plugin which is disabled by default to cycle your "master_seed" with the added ability of being able to login to a specific account to manage a board for instance. Be warned though that changing your username means you'll lose access to editing your old posts and your board, so make backups.
